  "title": "Analytics Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Description</strong></p><p>AddVita offers a lasting home for small and medium-sized healthcare distribution businesses across Asia, with a focus on acquiring and developing market-leading niche businesses. With a long-term vision and decentralized management, AddVita emphasizes sustainable earnings growth and robust cash flow. Backed by SeaTown Holdings International Pte. Ltd., AddVita benefits from the expertise of a leading Asia-focused alternative investment firm.</p><p><strong>Role Description</strong></p><p>This is a full-time on-site role for an Analytics Project Manager based in Singapore. This role's initial priority will involve building and implementing a strategic and proprietary analytical tool across various system platforms catered to AddVita's business and investment objectives. This role will help oversee all IT Finance initiatives across AddVita's group of Companies and is expected to bring further tech and system integration expertise to the AddVita team. We are looking for an experienced hire >5 years but high performing junior candidates with strong experiences are also welcomed to apply.</p><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>High proficiency in Data Analytics and Information Technology, with an understanding of tech solutions applicable to finance-related projects</li><li>Experienced with system integration, building of data lakes and warehouses, ETL processes, managing and implementing analytical tools</li><li>Decent experience in understanding finance, accounting, inventory operations and management</li><li>Excellent communication skills to engage with cross-functional teams, stakeholders, and management effectively</li><li>Proven ability to handle multiple priorities and deliver results under tight deadlines</li><li>Bachelor's degree or Diploma in Data Analytics, IT Systems, Computer Science, or a related field</li></ul>",
